    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_82077094" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/82077094" />
    <a title="Lori" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/744602-lori"><img alt="Lori" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1357149372p2/744602.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/82077094?book_show_action=true">Dec 26, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lori" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lori" href="/user/show/744602-lori">Lori</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer82077094" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2579198106495802262">It&apos;s taking me a long time to read this. Not because it&apos;s bad. Just the opposite. The writing is so exquisite that my heart is breaking over and over again and I realize I&apos;m not making the time to read. Yet I&apos;m drawn back every day, and then wonder why I&apos;m avoiding it. Against the backdrop of the brutality and idiocy of war, the beauty of life and the spirit are awesome, awesome as in the mysterious majesty that raises us to ecstasy.<br/><br/>100 more pages and I don&apos;t want it to end.<br/><br/>Breathtaking. My god </span>
  <span id="freeText2579198106495802262" style="display:none">It's taking me a long time to read this. Not because it's bad. Just the opposite. The writing is so exquisite that my heart is breaking over and over again and I realize I'm not making the time to read. Yet I'm drawn back every day, and then wonder why I'm avoiding it. Against the backdrop of the brutality and idiocy of war, the beauty of life and the spirit are awesome, awesome as in the mysterious majesty that raises us to ecstasy.<br /><br />100 more pages and I don't want it to end.<br /><br />Breathtaking. My god the man can write. I'm in a void right now, left to wonder what can I possibly read next that won't shatter under the reverberations lingering from finishing this book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2579198106495802262" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

